TITLE: Passing Parameters Between Screens - React Navigation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to navigate between screens in a React Native app using React Navigation while passing route parameters. It uses functional components and hooks such as useNavigation, and shows reading params from the route prop, passing new params via navigation.navigate and navigation.push, and configuring a simple stack navigator. Dependencies include react-native, @react-navigation/native, and @react-navigation/native-stack. The inputs are navigation actions; outputs are the rendered params on the destination screen and navigation transitions.
