TITLE: Accessing Theme in Dynamic NavigationContainer - React Navigation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to use the useTheme hook within a dynamic NavigationContainer to access and apply theme colors based on the system color scheme. It sets up stack and drawer navigators using the usual imperative approach, handles theme switching via useColorScheme, and applies colors throughout the UI components. Dependencies are react-navigation/native, react-navigation/drawer, react-navigation/native-stack, and react-native. All screens and custom components dynamically respond to theme changes provided by the container.
