TITLE: Passing Params Back to Previous Screen - React Navigation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code illustrates a pattern where data is passed back to the previous route from a navigated screen using navigation.popTo. It sets up a HomeScreen that reacts to param changes via useEffect and a CreatePostScreen that calls navigation.popTo to send the post data back. Dependencies include react-native, @react-navigation/native, and @react-navigation/native-stack. The expected input is user interaction in a TextInput; output is an alert showing the new post and a UI update.
