TITLE: Creating a Custom Action Creator Function (insertBeforeLast)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a reusable helper function `insertBeforeLast` which acts as a custom action creator. It accepts a `routeName` and optional `params`, takes the current navigation `state`, constructs a new routes array inserting the specified route before the last one, and returns a `CommonActions.reset` action object reflecting this change. Requires `CommonActions` from `@react-navigation/native`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x/navigation-prop.md#2025-04-23_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { CommonActions } from '@react-navigation/native';

const insertBeforeLast = (routeName, params) => (state) => {
  const routes = [
    ...state.routes.slice(0, -1),
    { name: routeName, params },
    state.routes[state.routes.length - 1],
  ];

  return CommonActions.reset({
    ...state,
    routes,
    index: routes.length - 1,
  });
};
```

