TITLE: Implementing an Authentication Loading Screen in React Native (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines a React component that boots up the authentication state by retrieving a token from AsyncStorage. Based on the token's existence, it navigates to either the App or authentication flow, unmounting itself afterwards. Requires React Native (react, react-native), AsyncStorage, and React Navigation's navigation prop. Accepts no input, initiates asynchronous check on mount, and displays a loading indicator during the process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-4.x/auth-flow.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
