TITLE: Passing and Retrieving Parameters in React Navigation
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to pass parameters when navigating to a new screen and how to retrieve those parameters in the destination screen. It includes examples of using navigation.navigate() with params and navigation.getParam() to access the passed data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-3.x/params.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
class HomeScreen extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <View style={{ flex: 1, alignItems: 'center', justifyContent: 'center' }}>
        <Text>Home Screen</Text>
        <Button
          title="Go to Details"
          onPress={() => {
            /* 1. Navigate to the Details route with params */
            this.props.navigation.navigate('Details', {
              itemId: 86,
              otherParam: 'anything you want here',
            });
          }}
        />
      </View>
    );
  }
}

class DetailsScreen extends React.Component {
  render() {
    /* 2. Get the param, provide a fallback value if not available */
    const { navigation } = this.props;
