TITLE: Resetting Navigation State with Custom Logic in React Navigation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This advanced example demonstrates dispatching a function to update the navigation state dynamically, removing all screens after the 'Profile' screen. It leverages a state transformation function in navigation.dispatch and constructs a reset action with the new state. This requires '@react-navigation/native' and assumes access to the navigation object. Inputs are the current state object; outputs are custom navigation states returned by the function. This approach avoids mutating the original state and must only rely on 'index' and 'routes' unless absolutely necessary.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x/navigation-actions.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
import { CommonActions } from '@react-navigation/native';

navigation.dispatch((state) => {
  // Remove all the screens after `Profile`
  const index = state.routes.findIndex((r) => r.name === 'Profile');
  const routes = state.routes.slice(0, index + 1);

  return CommonActions.reset({
    ...state,
    routes,
    index: routes.length - 1,
  });
});
```

