TITLE: Sample Router State Structure in React Navigation (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet displays a sample navigation state structure for a custom router in React Navigation, illustrating the index, routes array, and expected route object parameters such as routeName and key. It is meant to guide implementing getStateForAction to return navigation state objects in the correct format. No third-party dependencies are required, but conventions of React Navigation must be followed: routes should have both a unique key and a routeName. The example input and output is a plain JavaScript object representing navigation state. Key constraints are adhering to the documented structure so React Navigation can interpret the state correctly.
