TITLE: Using useNavigationState with a Class Component via a Wrapper in JavaScript (React)
DESCRIPTION: Provides a pattern for using the `useNavigationState` hook with a React class component. A functional component wraps the class component, uses the hook to get the desired state (`routesLength`), and passes it down as a prop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x/use-navigation-state.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
class Profile extends React.Component {
  render() {
    // Get it from props
    const { routesLength } = this.props;
  }
}

// Wrap and export
export default function (props) {
  const routesLength = useNavigationState((state) => state.routes.length);

  return <Profile {...props} routesLength={routesLength} />;
}
```

