TITLE: Implementing Top Level Navigation with React References
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to implement navigation at the top level component using React refs. This pattern allows calling navigation methods directly from the component where the navigator is declared. This approach should only be used for top-level navigators.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-2.x/custom-navigator-overview.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { NavigationActions } from 'react-navigation';

const AppNavigator = createStackNavigator(SomeAppRouteConfigs);

class App extends React.Component {
  someEvent() {
    // call navigate for AppNavigator here:
    this.navigator &&
      this.navigator.dispatch(
        NavigationActions.navigate({ routeName: someRouteName })
      );
  }
  render() {
    return (
      <AppNavigator
        ref={(nav) => {
          this.navigator = nav;
        }}
      />
    );
  }
}
```

