TITLE: Using useNavigationState with Class Components via Wrapper (React Navigation, JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to provide route length information as a prop to a class component by creating a functional wrapper that uses useNavigationState. The wrapper collects the number of routes from the navigation state and passes it to the Profile class component via props. This pattern allows usage of hooks in setups where class components cannot directly use them. Requires @react-navigation/native and React.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-5.x/use-navigation-state.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
class Profile extends React.Component {
  render() {
    // Get it from props
    const { routesLength } = this.props;
  }
}

// Wrap and export
