TITLE: Applying a Custom Scroll Offset with useScrollToTop (React Native)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to customize the scroll-to-top behavior by providing a specific scroll offset. A primary ref (`ref`) is created and attached to the `ScrollView`. Instead of passing this ref directly to `useScrollToTop`, a new ref object is created inline using `React.useRef`. This new object contains a custom `scrollToTop` function which, when invoked, calls the `scrollTo` method on the actual `ScrollView` ref (`ref.current`) with a specified vertical offset (`{ y: 100 }`).
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x/use-scroll-to-top.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { ScrollView } from 'react-native';
import { useScrollToTop } from '@react-navigation/native';

function Albums() {
  const ref = React.useRef(null);

  useScrollToTop(
    React.useRef({
      scrollToTop: () => ref.current?.scrollTo({ y: 100 }),
    })
  );

  return <ScrollView ref={ref}>{/* content */}</ScrollView>;
}
```

