TITLE: Describing Nested Navigation State with Stack and Tab Navigators (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet expands upon the previous one by showcasing a navigation state object that includes a nested tab navigator inside a stack navigator. The inner 'state' property embedded within a route's object indicates the child navigator's state, demonstrating support for composite navigation structures. This pattern requires no extra dependencies and is applicable when nesting navigators (e.g., stack containing tabs) in a React Navigation setup.
SOURCE: https://github.com/react-navigation/react-navigation.github.io/blob/main/versioned_docs/version-6.x/navigation-state.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const state = {
  type: 'stack',
  key: 'stack-1',
  routeNames: ['Home', 'Profile', 'Settings'],
  routes: [
    {
      key: 'home-1',
      name: 'Home',
      state: {
        key: 'tab-1',
        routeNames: ['Feed', 'Library', 'Favorites'],
        routes: [
          { key: 'feed-1', name: 'Feed', params: { sortBy: 'latest' } },
          { key: 'library-1', name: 'Library' },
          { key: 'favorites-1', name: 'Favorites' },
        ],
        index: 0,
      },
    },
    { key: 'settings-1', name: 'Settings' },
  ],
  index: 1,
};
```

